  "prompt": "How do bottle caps work in Pokemon Sun / Moon?",
  "response": "In Pok\u00e9mon Sun and Moon, bottle caps are special items used to enhance a Pok\u00e9mon's stats through a feature called Hyper Training. Here\u2019s how they work:\n\n1. **What are Bottle Caps?**\n   - Bottle caps are items you can find throughout the Alola region. There are two types of bottle caps: regular bottle caps and gold bottle caps. Regular bottle caps can be used to max out one specific stat (Attack, Defense, Special Attack, Special Defense, Speed, or HP) of a Pok\u00e9mon. Gold bottle caps, on the other hand, can be used to max out all six stats of a Pok\u00e9mon.\n\n2. **How to Obtain Bottle Caps:**\n   - You can find bottle caps in various locations throughout the game, such as through exploring, in hidden items, or as rewards in certain events. You can also receive them as gifts or through completing certain tasks.\n\n3. **Using Bottle Caps:**\n   - To use bottle caps, you must seek out an NPC known as the Meta-Royale Master, located in the Hau'oli City Shopping District. This character will perform Hyper Training for you.\n   - When you talk to the NPC, you can choose a Pok\u00e9mon from your party or box to train. You then select which stat you want to enhance (for regular bottle caps) or choose to enhance all stats (for gold bottle caps).\n\n4. **Limitations:**\n   - Hyper Training is available for Pok\u00e9mon that are level 100, so you cannot use bottle caps on lower-level Pok\u00e9mon. Additionally, Hyper Training does not affect a Pok\u00e9mon's base stats or its performance in competitive play in terms of its actual numerical stats; it only allows the trained stats to be considered as maxed out for battles.\n\n5. **Effect on Battles:**\n   - Once a Pok\u00e9mon has undergone Hyper Training, it will perform as if its stats are increased, making it more competitive in battles.\n\nOverall, bottle caps and Hyper Training are great features for trainers looking to optimize their Pok\u00e9mon's abilities and performance in battles.",
